comments.body:
I guess it is to avoid the compiler warning. If you do not assign it to `_`, you get:
```
libs-scala/scala-utils/src/main/scala/com/daml/scalautil/Statement.scala:14: warning: parameter value evaluateForSideEffectOnly in method discard is never used
  @specialized def discard[A](evaluateForSideEffectOnly: A): Unit = {
```

@S11001001 do you know if there is any other reason?

In any case the entire function has been "borrowed" from the `NonUnitStatements` wartremover docs:
http://www.wartremover.org/doc/warts.html

diffHunk:
